Sentencas: Thermal residual stresses are analyzed in SOFC components, especially in conditions when electrolyte and cathode layers are attached to other system components at different temperatures.
Titulo: Residual stress distribution in solid oxide fuel cells: anode-electrolyte and anode-electrolyte-cathode systems

Sentencas: The residual stress calculations were shown to agree with experimental data.
Titulo: Residual stress distribution in solid oxide fuel cells: anode-electrolyte and anode-electrolyte-cathode systems

Sentencas: Upon successively joining layers at different temperatures, the anode-electrolyte system has a noticeable curvature when attaching the cathode.
Titulo: Residual stress distribution in solid oxide fuel cells: anode-electrolyte and anode-electrolyte-cathode systems

Sentencas: Microcracking in individual elements of the fuel cell can be predicted through evaluation of residual stresses in anode-electrolyte (half-cell) and anode-electrolyte-cathode (full cell) systems.
Titulo: Residual stress distribution in solid oxide fuel cells: anode-electrolyte and anode-electrolyte-cathode systems
